attributes.name: name
attributes.value: Group Project – Digital Transformation Case Study Analysis (copy)

attributes.name: intro
attributes.value: Working in your assigned groups, prepare a comprehensive analysis of the digital transformation case study you selected earlier (Google, Siemens, or IKEA). Your report should demonstrate how course concepts apply to a real-world organizational setting.

attributes.name: activity
attributes.value:
Your submission must include the following sections:

  1. Introduction to the organization and context

  2. The digital transformation strategy applied

  3. Key technologies and tools used (e.g., AI, Cloud, Digital Twins)

  4. Business process changes (modeled in BPMN if applicable)

  5. Outcomes, lessons learned, and critical evaluation

  6. Conclusion and recommendations

Guidelines:

  • Length: 2000–2500 words

  • Format: PDF or DOCX

  • Include references (APA style)

  • All group members must contribute and will be asked to submit peer evaluations

attributes.name: name
attributes.value: Individual Report – Evaluating a Digital Transformation Case

attributes.name: intro
attributes.value:
Description:
Write a 1000–1200 word report analyzing a real-world example of digital transformation within an organization of your choice. Your report should address:

  • The organization’s background and context

  • The technologies involved

  • The business processes affected

  • Challenges and outcomes of the transformation

  • Your critical reflection on the success of the initiative

attributes.name: activity
attributes.value:
Instructions:

  • Use APA style for references.

  • Submit your report in PDF or DOCX format.

  • This is an individual assignment. No group work is allowed.

Submission Type:

  • File upload only (PDF or DOCX)

  • Max number of uploaded files: 1

  • Max file size: 10 MB
